Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Knidian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay medium red-brown. Rectangular stamp with horse head symbol.
Type series: KT1652 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 201, 14 Names, Pythokritos, Tenades.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0338)
